@infinity I need to look up meta. If he doesn't have past games I'd call him newb town at this point, but I do think he could be scum trying to force us to look at his reads on lurkers rather than his more relevant reads. Will go through more tonight. Just finishing out the work day now.<br>
<br>
@telo I WAS trying to help you, I was also calling you out... sorry if that's hard to understand. That is my opinion of what you did. I think exactly what inifinity said. Lurking scum has to come out at some point. Look at the content for reads rather than the non-content. Nothing drives me more crazy than people who try to use something that doesn't exist to support their read. Most scum show it in their content, and its still early in the game so there is no reason to call them out. Also, There's no reason to call me suspicious if you find me null, that's what i'm trying to say with your read on me. I do find that if you are detracting from the what you are saying as your actual reads, than you are detracting from the game. You're putting content in there that is useless which could be to take the spotlight away from your other reads, and it also causes us to talk about your reads and explain to you that they are null and not suspicious rather than talk about content that others have been posting.

@bud I disagree. I was trying to fully explain myself. If I hadn't been detailed you would have had to ask questions<br>
<br>
@mechron you missed me <img class="smilies" src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" width="15" height="15" alt=":)" title="Smile">

